The paper discusses the use of computational topology and spectral methods for analyzing complex datasets modeled as simplicial complexes. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of generalized Cheeger inequalities and isoperimetric inequalities, which are topics in computational geometry and topology, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper introduces a method for sparsifying simplicial complexes, which involves solving linear systems, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible category.
